metadata.name: Julia's Magical Bulbs - 3rd 4th 5th Powers #94
metadata.description:
Julia's Magical Bulbs are 3D dimensional fractals, based on the Julia Sets of the Mandelbulb fractal.  In this edition we explore the 3rd, 4th and 5th powers.

The token is interactive, use your mouse-wheel to zoom-in and see all the little details. You will find a menu in the lower-right corner which allows you to play with the iterations and camera position. You can also render high-resolution images here.

A little bit of magic happens when you select low iteration values, perhaps your token will even default to this.

Technical:

Not all browsers support multi-threaded modules, the fallback mode is quite slow. Try Chrome if your browser is not supported.

Calculated in full 64-bit on the CPU (not the GPU) for more accurate and detailed images.

metadata.name: Toccata #197
metadata.description:
Toccata is a piece about decay, about the impermanent. The emergence over time or, rather, progression of entropy is a key characteristic of our universe. Everything evolves to nothing. We as mortal beings have sometimes trouble reconciling with this idea. Humans have sought immortality for millennia, be it through ancient potions or modern medicine, be it from leaving a legacy that we feel will stand the test of time. It will, only to decay later than us.

Toccata is a piece about change. Change lies at the heart of human cognition and human nature. Our thoughts and our emotions happen over time, and are a function of the change that is both around us and at the very core of our selves. Change comes in nature in cycles. Seasons of growth, seasons of ripe fruits of life, seasons of decay, of death, rebirth.

Toccata is music. We find music to convey some of the deepest streams of human condition, connecting it to some other form of being. Music also happens over time, and music happens because of change. Music encodes our feelings better than any other aid we may have. Toccata incorporates this at its very core, as the main sound is Andreas' family piano where he learned to play, sampled this past July.

Read more about the piece, and the collaboration between Marcelo and Andreas on andreasrau.eu/toccata

---

Basic controls:
- Click on the piece or press spacebar to start it (WebAudio requires user intervention for the music to start). Once the music has started, again click or press spacebar to play/pause.
- Press “s” to save a still at the current resolution
- Press “r” to start recording a video at the current resolution, then “r” again to stop.

---

WebM audio-video recording performed using the library RecordRTC by https://muazkhan.com/, MIT licence.

metadata.name: VOYAGERS #105
metadata.description:
Generative animated painting made from looping gestures in a virtual void.

Voyagers is an exploration of automated gestures and screenspace layering effects. Each brush stroke sweeps through the canvas leaving a trail of color that either disappears or mixes with adjacent colors. The image slowly builds up to achieve an equilibrium between the rhythm of the gestures and the interaction of color values. These colors are quantized and dithered to produce chunky, textured, blocks of light that reify the materiality of the screen and the pixel. Two aspect ratios are possible, each with its own material relationship to screen-based work, 1:1 and 4:3 (vertical).

Press 's' to save looping animated GIF (live mode only).
Press 'p' to pause the animation.
Press 'c' to capture a single frame.
Made with P5.js and GLSL. By @galoandstuff.

metadata.name: Grift Graft #159
metadata.description:
"Grift Graft" is an experimental generative art piece that attempts to highlight some of the inherent contradictions surrounding the discussion of non-fungible tokens (NFTs) and its place as a vehicle for artistic creation, artistic expression and the potential of remuneration for artists.

To the extent possible, source code is dedicated to the public domain (CC0). Third party libraries are used that are not CC0 but are libre/free licensed, allowing for commercial reuse (see source for details). Artwork is copyright Caleb Harrington and is used with permission under a CC-BY-SA (3.0) license.

"Grift Graft" attempts to subvert the narrative that NFTs are only a vehicle for theft by offering a generative NFT that can be minted at no cost. "Grift Graft" offers an NFT to anyone that wants one, free of charge.

This work hopes to add to the conversation about examining the reality of the ecosystem that we've developed around digital goods and intellectual property.

metadata.name: 4rtiu5 #1
metadata.description:
Wiki

A circle is a shape consisting of all points in a plane that are at a given distance from a given point, the centre. Equivalently, it is the curve traced out by a point that moves in a plane so that its distance from a given point is constant. The distance between any point of the circle and the centre is called the radius.

Name

So, I kinda have a thing with language so I tried to find a funny mix of "art" or "genart" and "circle" or "radius".
I ended up using "radius", scrambled it a bit which became "arduis" and replace "ard" with "art". 
The 4 and the S mean like "4 us", hence "4rtiu5" :-)

Project

There aren't much properties that are set, except for "dashed lines" and "blurred gutters". I had a lot of fun making this and was amazed by some really great outputs myself, I hope you guys like it too! :-)
Cheers 🍻
